{"title": "Leakage of sensitive data in JWT", "summary": "  JWTs are not a secure place to store sensitive data. This rule looks for any sensitive data types saved to a JWT. ", "description": "\n\nJWTs are not a secure place to store sensitive data. This rule looks for any sensitive data types saved to a JWT.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid storing sensitive data in JWT:\n\n```php\n$payload = [\n  'data' => 'data',\n  'email' => $user->email\n];\n$jwt = JWT::encode($payload, $key, 'HS256');\n```\n\n\u2705 If you need to store user's information, use their unique database identifier instead of personal identifiable information:\n\n```php\n$payload = [\n  'data' => 'data',\n  'uuid' => $user->uuid\n];\n$jwt = JWT::encode($payload, $key, 'HS256');\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-315"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_jwt"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}